					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Sumez wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">There is no way I can play Super Metroid or any of the Mega Man X games without changing the controls first.</div><br />The funny thing is that I actually like the default controls in Super Metroid (granted, I'm not a speedrunner):<br /><br />A - Jump<br />X - Shoot<br />B - Run<br /><br />What this does is it basically gives you two easily accessible buttons just to the left of the jump button. Super Mario Bros. had A to jump and B to run. NES Metroid had A to jump and B to shoot. Both have the action to the left of jump. Why not combine those two (without button cramming of course)?<br /><br />For games that use the more common &quot;B to jump, Y to run/shoot&quot; scheme, I prefer having A as a tertiary/super. You won't hit it by accident but it's still within reach. Unless you need to use X for something, in which case it raises the likelihood of hitting A by accident.<br /><br />In any case though, yes, please allow rebinding the controls.</div>

					
